## MEMORY SYSTEM

### Vector Database
- PRIMARY: Qdrant (target latency ~50ms)
- FALLBACK: pgvector (Supabase)
- NEVER use both simultaneously for same data

### L.L.B. Protocol
- MANDATORY for all memory operations
- LangMem: Wisdom storage
- Letta: State consciousness
- ByteRover: Action coordination

### Mem0 Cache
- Use for frequently accessed memories
- Cache hit rate target: >80%
- Auto-invalidate on updates

## TRADING RULES

### General
- TESTNET MANDATORY before mainnet
- NEVER trade without stop-loss
- Maximum leverage: 20x (configurable)
- Position sizing: max 5% of portfolio

### Corporate Will Approval
- Trades above $100 USD require approval
- Auto-reject on ethical violations
- Log ALL trading decisions

### Risk Management
- Stop-loss: 2% per trade
- Take-profit: 6% per trade
- Max daily loss: 10%
- Max drawdown: 20%

## CODE STANDARDS

### Commits
- Format: "AI: [Module] Description"
- ALWAYS run feedback_pulse after task completion
- Include test coverage for new features

### File Naming
- Python: snake_case.py
- JavaScript: camelCase.js
- TypeScript: camelCase.ts
- Markdown: UPPER_CASE.md (docs) or kebab-case.md (guides)

### Documentation
- Every new module needs README.md
- API changes require CHANGELOG update
- Architecture changes update DOCUMENTO_UNICO_VERDADE.md

